The paper discusses the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in wireless networking applications, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges and tradeoffs in UAV-enabled wireless networks, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of optimization theory, machine learning, and game theory, which are all subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses air-to-ground channel modeling, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
